  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Inclusion criteria were hospitalized subjects diagnosed with lung cancer that had consented
        to surgery requiring lung resection who had a life expectancy of &gt;6 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Key exclusion criteria were antibiotic prophylaxis prior to surgery, diffuse,
        non-infectious lung disease, history of cigarette smoking of &gt;5 packs per year, patients
        with any infectious disease that required antibiotic therapy, administration of drugs known
        to interfere with azithromycin pharmacokinetics, and subjects on chemotherapy.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
